1771857276021736	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEylQE		item.comment	bn-2bh3	{"body":"Progress update:\nImplemented a real incremental PageRank path in crates/bones-triage/src/metrics/pagerank.rs with guarded fallback policy.\n\nWhat is in place:\n- Frontier + downstream affected-set incremental iteration\n- Global dangling-mass term during affected-node updates\n- Guarded fallback conditions (unknown/empty frontier, large affected set, item cardinality mismatch, dangling transition risk, dangling-mass drift, residual failure)\n- Method semantics preserved (Incremental vs IncrementalFallback)\n\nSecond pass completed:\n- Tightened dangling-transition heuristic to use SCC-pair item-edge counts from ng.raw (instead of naive source out-degree deltas)\n- Added unit tests to verify heuristic behavior for:\n  - non-transition parallel member addition in same SCC pair\n  - true first outgoing-edge transition\n\nValidation:\n- cargo test -p bones-triage --test pagerank\n- cargo test -p bones-triage\nAll passing."}	blake3:1PEu8zP92NBaKV25rx-T4lzviJaI-j_q_tc7d3GLQHo
1771857589714761	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEylgE		item.comment	bn-2bh3	{"body":"Added telemetry for incremental-vs-fallback observability.\n\nChanges:\n- crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/triage_support.rs now emits tracing logs for PageRank execution path:\n  - cache hit\n  - incremental success\n  - incremental fallback (warn)\n  - full recompute\n  Each log includes nodes/edges and relevant context (changes, iterations, converged).\n- crates/bones-triage/tests/pagerank.rs performance test now prints method distribution and fallback rate for the sampled workload:\n  - incremental count\n  - fallback count\n  - full count\n  - fallback_rate (%)\n\nThis gives immediate visibility into whether the incremental path is actually being used and how often fallback is triggered."}	blake3:j2s43VxpfLSq7BunEI1aJHUYrx1cfcKcjmImo1X_lMU
1771857781257544	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEylwE		item.comment	bn-2bh3	{"body":"Tuning pass completed based on telemetry.\n\nAdjustments in incremental pagerank:\n- Reduced conservative fallback pressure while preserving correctness:\n  - affected-set fallback threshold changed from 50% -> 80%\n  - removed hard fallback on item-cardinality mismatch (incremental now seeds defaults + normalization)\n  - dangling transition now promotes to global affected-set (before threshold check)\n- Retained strict safety checks to protect accuracy:\n  - dangling-mass drift fallback remains at tolerance * 10\n  - global residual fallback remains at tolerance * 10\n\nObserved telemetry from performance harness (same workload as before):\n- Fallback rate dropped from ~56% to ~20%\n- Method mix now shows substantially more Incremental runs\n\nValidation:\n- cargo test -p bones-triage --test pagerank\n- cargo test -p bones-triage\n- cargo test -p bones-cli triage_support\nAll passing."}	blake3:i0l8z2Bjme32JtaWBGjA49nXbjM50dAos4UyC3GGflg
