1771870025514663	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEymQE		item.create	bn-7jpm	{"description":"`bn create` can emit `duplicate check failed: lexical search failed` on valid punctuation-heavy titles (for example colons and em dashes). Creation succeeds, but warning is noisy/misleading and especially confusing in freshly initialized repos.\n\nRepro\n1) `bn init`\n2) `bn create --title \"Spike: Walking skeleton — ward review end-to-end on trivial case\" ...`\n3) Observe warning in stderr\n\nExpected\n- Duplicate detection sanitizes/tokenizes input before FTS\n- Valid punctuation does not cause lexical-search warnings\n- Duplicate check degrades gracefully (skip when no usable tokens) without WARN noise\n\nAcceptance criteria\n- Repro above no longer emits warning\n- Duplicate detection still catches obvious near-duplicates on normal titles\n- Tests cover punctuation-heavy create path","kind":"bug","labels":["cli","search","duplicate-check"],"size":"s","title":"Fix create duplicate-check warning on punctuation-heavy titles"}	blake3:vdchK7nyKOA9yB-rgdVaU7__44F2Z2EgbedWv60omBI
1771870576151760	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEymgE		item.create	bn-167i	{"description":"Problem\nIn dependency chains where an urgent item is blocked, triage does not surface its prerequisites as top actionable work. Example from ~/src/ward: bn-39t is urgent and depends on bn-3fq, but bn next/triage do not consistently prioritize bn-3fq as the top ready item.\n\nObserved behavior\n- Dependency edge exists correctly: bn-3fq -> bn-39t\n- bn show reflects blockers/dependents correctly\n- bn next ranks by local score among unblocked items, so prerequisite urgency is not propagated\n- bn triage blocker section is sorted mostly by unblocks count + local score, not urgency pressure from blocked descendants\n\nExpected behavior\n- If item X is urgent and blocked by Y, and Y is actionable, Y should receive strong priority pressure and appear at/near top in bn next and triage top picks.\n- Prioritization should respect dependency execution order for urgent chains.\n\nLikely root cause\nCurrent scoring is largely local:\n- composite_score urgency applies only to the item itself\n- active_unblocks is count-based, not urgency-weighted\n- bn next uses unblocked_ranked local scores without upstream urgency propagation\n\nProposed solution (detailed)\n1) Add urgency-pressure propagation metric\n   - Build a derived score for each node from blocked descendants (preferably over reverse dependency edges).\n   - Seed pressure from descendant urgency/state (Urgent >> Default >> Punt).\n   - Decay by hop distance (e.g., geometric factor) and optionally damp by branching.\n\n2) Integrate into triage scoring\n   - Add a new metric term in RankedItem scoring path (or augment unblocks signal) that lifts prerequisites of urgent blocked items.\n   - Keep bounded normalization so scores remain stable and deterministic.\n\n3) Update bn next selection behavior\n   - Ensure next uses propagated pressure when choosing among ready items.\n   - Preserve current exclusion rules (done/archived, blocked items not directly selectable unless command semantics change).\n\n4) Improve explanations\n   - Add explanation text like: \"Prioritized because it unblocks urgent item(s): bn-39t\" or summarized count.\n\n5) Add guardrails\n   - Avoid over-prioritizing distant prerequisites in deep chains via distance decay cap.\n   - Keep deterministic ordering tie-breakers unchanged where possible.\n\nAcceptance criteria\n- Repro graph: A(urgent, blocked by B). B is ready. bn next returns B.\n- Multi-hop graph: A(urgent) <- B <- C. B outranks unrelated defaults; C gets weaker uplift than B via decay.\n- Existing non-blocked urgent behavior remains correct (urgent ready items still top).\n- Triage explanations explicitly mention urgent-unblock driver when applicable.\n- New tests cover:\n  - urgent blocked single-hop propagation\n  - multi-hop decay behavior\n  - no propagation from done/archived blocked descendants\n  - deterministic tie-breaking with equal propagated pressure\n\nSuggested touchpoints\n- crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/triage_support.rs\n- crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/next.rs\n- crates/bones-triage/src/score/* (if metric extracted there)\n- triage/next tests in bones-cli and/or bones-triage\n\nNotes\nThis is a prioritization semantics bug, not a dependency storage bug. Edges are stored correctly; ranking policy needs dependency-aware urgency propagation.","kind":"bug","labels":["triage","next","dependencies","urgency"],"size":"l","title":"Triage: propagate urgent blocked-item priority to prerequisite blockers"}	blake3:XuWlJ830lqDsRlJKoRK95aJUc-uz5yTZ5utjX2WzT9Q
